unit.name: 12 Volksgrenadier Division HQ
unit.History: The 12th Volksgrenadier Division was formed in October 1944 from the remnants of the 12th Infantry Division, which was destroyed on the Eastern Front in July 1944. At the start of 'Wacht am Rhein' the 12th VGD was considered the best infantry division of the 6th Panzer Army. Like all Volksgrenadier Divisions, the 12th had six infantry battalions in three infantry regiments, but one of its infantry regiments had the honorific title of 'Fusilier Regiment'.

commander.PersBio: Born in 1904, Holz served with 3rd coy, 258thPz Jg Abt of the 258th Infantry Division in Russia, earning the Knight's Cross in 1943. He was transferred to the 12th VGD, and commanded the 12th Pz Jg Abt.
